author_ssm: Finding aid prepared by Miriam Berkin, January 1992
abstract_ssm: This collection consists of the personal papers of Helen A. Murphy (1889-1986), children's author and playwright, and director of the Children's Theatre Program at Greenwich House from 1923-1968. The papers date from 1914 to 1986. The bulk are from her tenure at Greenwich House, and include short stories, scripts, promotional material, correspondence, administrative material and some personal effects. The collection is organized into three series: The Children's and Adult's Theatre at Greenwich House; Writings and Other Activities; and Personal Material.
corpname_ssm: Tamiment Library and Robert F. Wagner Labor Archives
